hits.description: Contains a list of all insurance companies that can be selected for an insurance record. Additional insurance companies can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

hits.description: Contains all contact types associated with a case. These types can be changed with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

Contains all shareholder types associated with a business that must have a corresponding license. This is commonly used when an owner or person in charge of the organization must have a license. These types can be changed with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

Contains all shareholder types associated with a business shareholder. Additional parameters include whether or not the shareholder type is required for a business and the display ordinal of the list of shareholders. These types can be changed with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.
This entity will be used to configure any fees required during a Business License Reinstatement, based on the Business License Type and Destination Status.

port_customprocesstypeid.description: Arranging custom process in navigation tab

hits.description: Contains a list of all navigation links that may appear within a portal and their associated category. Parameters include the link name, ordinal, the associated portal, associated portal page, and any display condition metadata.

Contains all custom process types. A custom process is any process that has a series of steps to submit information and an approval or rejection. The custom process is the container that captures the necessary information for a process and stores it in an alternate entity. The custom process additional parameters such as name, description, JSON metadata, associated portal, parent custom process if applicable, enabling a single process at a time or multiple processes in sequence and a description.

Contains a list of categories that are used to categorized the navigation that appears in the portal. Additional navigation categories can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

Contains all files that have been posted in a resource library and their associated descriptions and category for committee members.
Contains all vote types that could be cast associated with a board meeting motion vote. Additional vote type can be added with no system impact during initial configuration.

tc_name.description: This is required. Enter a unique name for the unit of measurement that can be used for the program units.

hits.description: Contains a list of units of measurement for continuing education programs. Typically, this will be hours or credits.

Contains all statuses associated with an individual's continuing education program. Additional statuses should not added. 
ALL STATUSES ARE SYSTEM STATUSES AND CANNOT BE CHANGED: 
Open - the plan is open and can be modified, 
Closed - the plan is closed and can no longer be modified, 
Submitted - the plan has been submitted to the regulator.

Contains all statuses available when a continuing education exemption has been requested. Additional statuses can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations. 
THE SYSTEM DEFAULT CANNOT BE CHANGED: 
Exempted

Contains all individual license reinstatement application statuses. Additional statuses can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations. 
THE SYSTEM DEFAULT STATUSES CANNOT BE CHANGED: 
New - the reinstatement has been started but not yet submitted, 
Submitted - the reinstatement has been submitted by the individual, 
Rejected - the reinstatement has been rejected by the regulator, 
Approved - license changes are processed.

cust_supervisor_end_date.description: This date field is a text field as per client specific request

cust_supervisor_start_date.description: This date field is a text field as per client specific request

hits.description: Contains all statuses for supervision agreements. Additional supervision agreement statuses can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations. THE SYSTEM DEFAULT STATUSES CANNOT BE CHANGED: Requested - requested by the supervisee as part of an application to the regulator, Active - an active agreement approved by the regulator.

Related to the business license application type, Contains application instructions contains presented to a business in the business portal as a standard page when starting an application. Connected to the business application instructions are application documents which are also displayed on the application instructions page.

lrn_active.description: This is required. Select ?Yes? to indicate that this activity type is active and can be selected as a program activity in the continuing education plan. It is inactive when set to ?No?.

lrn_activity_maximum_units.description: Enter the maximum units allowed for this activity type.

lrn_activity_minimum_units.description: Enter the minimum units allowed for this activity type.

lrn_activity_total_maximum_units.description: Enter the total number of maximum units acquired for this activity type.

lrn_activityproviderid.description: Select the continuing education provider of the professional development activity from the CE Activity Provider entity if "Use Provider List" is required or set to "Yes" in the Continuing Education Configuration section of the Portal Configuration.

lrn_ask_additional_questions.description: Select "Yes" to indicate that additional questions will be asked for this activity type. Additional question will not be asked when set to "No".

lrn_description.description: Enter the description of how this activity type is used. This is displayed internally.

lrn_require_documentation.description: Select ?Yes? to indicate that additional documentation is required for this activity type. Additional documentation is not required when set to ?No?.

port_stringresource_key.description: Enter the string resource key for the activity type name. This value is stored in the String Resources entity. This is used for language translation in multi-language systems.

tc_createdbyid.description: The pre-populated profile of the individual who created the activity type.

tc_modifiedbyid.description: The pre-populated profile of the individual who modified the activity type.

tc_name.description: Enter a unique name for the activity type.

tc_ownerid.description: The pre-populated profile of the individual who owns the activity type.

hits.description: Contains all activity types that can be selected associated with a continuing education activity entry. These activity types can be associated with an activity provider and can be activated and deactivated.

Contains all education institution types associated with educational institutions for individual education records. These types can be changed with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

Contains all categories of files for the board resource library. Additional resources categories can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

Contains all supervision evaluation statuses that are association with a supervisor evaluation and supervision agreement. Additional supervisor evaluation statuses can be added with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations. 
THE SYSTEM DEFAULT STATUSES CANNOT BE CHANGED: 
Not Submitted - the evaluation has been created but not submitted by the supervisee, 
Submitted - the evaluation has been submitted by the supervisee to the supervisor, 
Supervisor Approved - the supervisor has reviewed and provided approval on the evaluation report, 
Supervisor Rejected - the supervisor has rejected the evaluation report.

Contains all student change request types associated with a student change request and the required fee. These types can be changed with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations.

port_accessroleid.description: Defines the role granted the access

port_can_submit.description: Specifies that the role can update and submit the final page.

port_page_url.description: Defines the page the access applies to; takes the actual url or a regex

port_read_access.description: Control if this page can be seen/read E.g. Hide the item in the navigation bar.

port_write_access.description: Control if this page can be edited and submitted.

hits.description: Define access to pages by roles

Contains all practice hour report statuses associated with a student practice hour report submitted by a school. Additional student practice hour report statuses can be configured with no system impact on intial configuration. If the configuration records have been used in a production environment they should be removed with caution, as it could lead to orphaned processes and broken configurations. 
THE SYSTEM DEFAULT STATUSES CANNOT BE CHANGED: 
Submitted - submitted by the school to the regulator, 
Approved - practice hour reports reviewed and approved by the regulator.

Contains the configuration for fee(s) that will be charged in relation to the associated inspection checklist. Parameters include the name, and if the fee is charged on a passed inspection or a failed inspection.

Related to the individual authorization application instructions, this entity defines documents that are required to be submitted with an individual license application. Documents can also be required to be submitted to the agency directly by a third-party and will create an outstanding document record with the associated application on submission. Required documents appear on the supporting documents page in renewal. Additional parameters include the ordinal, document reference name, if the document must be uploaded or remitted, or if it can be optionally provided.
